6 MONITORING 
The Refuge is especially important as a migration corridor for neotropical migratory birds.
Current Refuge funding and staff does not allow the application of habitat management treatments and monitoring necessary to provide optimum habitat for wildlife.
This project would provide the funding necessary to hire and provide the infrastructure (residence, vehicle, equipment) for a Refuge biologist.
A residence would be constructed in year one.
An experienced biologist would be recruited in year two.
