60
Browns Park Comprehensive Conservation Plan - March 1999
9 HABITAT RESTORATION: Wetland Restoration MEASURES: 50 Refuge acres will be restored.
The Hoy wetland unit on the Refuge provides excellent habitat for great numbers and species of migrating and breeding waterfowl and waterbirds.
Approximately 50 small islets were created near the Hoy dike years ago.
Nest monitoring revealed that the nesting success of ducks on the islets was so low that they were a "sink" for the breeding population.
This project would fund the flattening of these islets to remove the sink.
The wetland would be drawn down until conditions are safe to use heavy equipment in the wetland basin.
A dozer and/or scraper would be used to level the islets.
Work would be contracted.
